  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf add a contact, join a random public without any history, and tap `@`, this contact will be suggested for mention even though they haven't joined it.\r\nIf send such a mention, it will be displayed in plain text.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"219\" alt=\"Screenshot 2022-03-28 at 16 26 05\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/160420072-c05f2996-d2ca-4aa8-8b23-8bcc640ca1d7.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCan only mention users who have joined a public chat\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nCan mention any contact\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Install Status\r\n2. Create an account\r\n3. Add a contact\r\n4. Join a random public chat (i.e. smth like #vjnfdlvjndfln)\r\n5. Type `@`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: RC 1.19\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
